					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/archaicglint" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1602267); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1602267&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183060" alt="ArchaicGlint" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1602267)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/archaicglint" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1602267); return false;" >ArchaicGlint</a></span> <span class="odate time_1366181242 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Apr 2013 06:47</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1754642">
									

<p>Interesting, but I feel like there's a plot hole.</p>
<p>How could the doctor, contain/kill Able like that with the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Able could have evaded the bullet</li>
<li>Able could have parried the bullet</li>
<li>I'm not sure about this but, Able could withstand more punishment even from a headshot.</li>
<li>The gun being too big to aim accurately</li>
<li>The doctor too shaky to aim it accurately</li>
</ul>
<p>I know this is kinda an old tale. But I really like it except that little plot hole</p>

							</div>

								
