																		Re: Is there a Plot hole?
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jukse" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1433010); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1433010&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183060" alt="Jukse" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1433010)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jukse" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1433010); return false;" >Jukse</a></span> <span class="odate time_1366204797 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Apr 2013 13:19</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1754739">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">A&nbsp;somewhat&nbsp;lengthy&nbsp;explanation.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">&nbsp;[R1]&nbsp;Hide,&nbsp;Ashley</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Well, the first and last two points you raised could be explained (In a somewhat lenient manner, that is), by this segment:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The man glared at her, fury growing at this effrontery. Those who had come before had been weaklings, but they had at least been warriors of a sort.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>From this, we can infer that 076-2 simply doesn't acknowledges Langley as a threat, disregarding the possibility that any of his inhuman acrobatics would be needed in order to finish off such a frail &quot;opponent&quot;. Sure, it's certainly debatable whether or not a shaken, untrained researcher would be able to take a shot under such mental strain, but it wouldn't be accurate to rule out this possibility either, given Able's recklessness.</p>
<p>That being said, let's take a look at <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-076">SCP-076</a> main page:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Take multiple .50 caliber BMG rounds to the head and survive for several minutes to continue killing, despite severe damage to the cerebellum.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>So, Able will continue to move after getting hit in the head by several of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/.50_BMG">these</a> things, which were likely fired from a modern equivalent of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M2_Browning_machine_gun">this</a> little thing, but immediately drop dead after being shot once by a pistol. Umm.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>TL;DR: Given that this is a tale, stories in which improbable things happen quite often, it's hardly fair to qualify this particular situation as a plot hole, but it's certainly iffy to assume that Langley, besides hitting Able in a lucky shot, would also be casually carrying around some kind of super OTT handgun capable of outclassing heavy MG's by such large, unrealistic margin.</p>

							</div>

								
					
