					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rain-gass" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4602872); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4602872&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183060" alt="Rain Gass" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4602872)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rain-gass" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4602872); return false;" >Rain Gass</a></span> <span class="odate time_1538521047 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Oct 2018 22:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4011505">
									

<p>I actually don't mind the ending; I know he's supposed to be superhuman to a point, but frankly it always felt more silly to me that he can tank multiple large-caliber BMG rounds to the head and keep functioning enough to be a threat. I get that 682 can do that because he's a regenerating alien eldritch lizard thing (Toffee, maybe?), but Able is technically still a human. I get that being so hard to kill is part of what makes him threatening, but once a person loses a large enough portion of brain, they really shouldn't be able to keep going.</p>
<p>I do enjoy this story, Crow, and I do hope you keep it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
